From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andrea <auguccioni15@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 1 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ram: stm32mp1: fix maybe-uninitialized warning for result

GCC's -Werror=maybe-uninitialized fires because execution can enter the
while body and reach uses of result (e.g. the printf at end:) without
passing through any assignment. Initialize to 0 (success) since the
function returns 0 on the happy path.

Signed-off-by: Andrea <auguccioni15@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/ram/stm32mp1/stm32mp1_interactive.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/ram/stm32mp1/stm32mp1_interactive.c b/drivers/ram/stm32mp1/stm32mp1_interactive.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/drivers/ram/stm32mp1/stm32mp1_interactive.c
+++ b/drivers/ram/stm32mp1/stm32mp1_interactive.c
@@ -333,7 +333,7 @@ static void stm32mp1_ddr_subcmd(struct ddr_info *priv,
 {
 	int i;
 	unsigned long value;
-	int result;
+	int result = 0;
 	char string[50] = "";

 	if (argc == 1) {
